extendedInfo.description: Ever want to skip the concession line instead of the game? With Bypass, you can order food and beverages at your favorite sporting or music event without ever waiting in line. Participating venues offer pick-up through a designated Bypass Lane and/or in-seat delivery. "It's like a toll-tag for tacos". - Television Sports BroadcasterFeatures:- Order Food and Beverages from your seat- Pick-up through a dedicated Bypass Lane - Food and drink delivered to your seat (where available)- Store multiple payment cards under a single password- No requirement to pre-register, place your first order at an eventVisit www.bypasslane.com for participating venues and additional information.Feedback:Have an idea for a future release? We welcome your suggestions, comments, and feedback. Email us: info@bypasslane.com

reviews.title: Works as described
reviews.comment: Tried this for the first time at Barclays Center yesterday. Seems to be a nicely organized system. My only complaint would be that there are no descriptions for the food items.

reviews.title: Works just fine at Xcel Energy Center!
reviews.comment: Every once in a while the app goes really slow and force closes, but for the most part it works great! You enter in your section, row, and seat you are at and it shows you all available bypass lane places in the building. Also, at each food place, there is a bright blue mat and is roped off to show you where you should go, so you dont wait in line. They text you when your order is ready and you walk up, to the small line, if there is a line at all, where the big bright blue mat that reads \"Bypass Lane\".
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: So Cool
reviews.comment: Got to our seats, took the order for all 6 of us, submitted the order, paid by ATM credit card that was already loaded onto the app (yes, it gives the option for a last minute change for someone else to pay), got a text message on my cell 5-7 mins later, walked to the concession stand, walked straight to the front in a private line for Bypass Orders, and right back to the seats.  What easily would have been a 20 minute loss of game time was only 5.  Very Cool!!!

reviews.title: Dont use at Excel Energy Center
reviews.comment: This application is useless. At least at the facility i used it at. I still had to wait in line to get my purchases  just like everyone else does. And besides that only 1 specific  person at the counter is able to process the bypass app. purchases. Yet they don\'t even have a sign that tells you what line is specifically for the bypass customers. I waited in one line for 5 minutes, got to the counter and was told that id have to go the other ebd of the counter which also had a line. It took over 10 mins.

reviews.title: Bypass? my a**
reviews.comment: Avoid this app unless your venue has their act together. Used this once since the venue had a $5 credit advertised. Never got the credit when I placed my first order, they charge a 99-cent fee, and for this fee I waited over 5 minutes for the staff to even acknowledge I was THE ONLY PERSON STANDING IN THE BYPASS LANE STARING AT THE TICKET PRINTER WITH MY ORDER ON IT! If I waited in the regular line they would have served me sooner and I\'d have saved the stupid (in)convenience fee. Uninstalling.

reviews.title: Would be good, except...
reviews.comment: The app now accesses your audio recorder, which is an unwarranted privacy intrusion - in theory it could record anything you say.  Also, the user agreement opts your email in for SPAM, you get no choice in the matter.  If it weren\'t for this, it would be a great app.  Will be uninstalling.  Don\'t need more spam spam spam spam....
